I think this is because when you run `tower server`, it's loading the script from the global installation, which looks like this:

[/bin/tower](https://github.com/viatropos/tower/blob/8da86586adbc3fd4193150945cf40722fe44a3c2/bin/tower)

```
#!/usr/bin/env node

require('../lib/tower').Command.run(process.argv);
```

That then tries to require all of the libraries from your global set of modules.  I haven't quite figured out a good way to do this, because when you do `tower new app` you _want_ it to use the global modules since the path is relative.  But when you do `tower console` and `tower server`, you don't.

It needs to be something like:

```
#!/usr/bin/env node

// process.argv == ['node', 'tower', 'server']
if (process.argv[2] && process.argv[2].match(/new/)
  require('../lib/tower').Command.run(process.argv);
else // will find from local node_modules
  require('tower').Command.run(process.argv);
```

